From 5cdbdc609f92112728d6b052e67a3466a27fa1dc Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Kapilash <kapilash@example.com>
Date: Tue, 21 Jul 2026 14:44:35 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Add Phase 1 knowledge engine: cited RAG search over Mars
 sources

Implements the roadmap's Phase 1 milestone (cited Mars knowledge-search
prototype) as retrieval-augmented search, not model training/fine-tuning
- see docs/KNOWLEDGE_ENGINE.md for the reasoning.

- mars_ai_os.knowledge: Document/Chunk/Citation/Answer models, sentence-
  boundary chunking, deterministic zero-dependency HashingEmbedder,
  InMemoryVectorStore, pluggable SourceConnector protocol (ships
  LocalCorpusConnector + StaticDocumentConnector), extractive
  citation-only Answerer by default (cannot hallucinate: Answer requires
  at least one citation by construction)
- KnowledgeService: Kernel-registerable Service (start/stop/health) that
  ingests configured connectors and answers questions with citations
- Optional, clearly-separated OllamaAnswerer (knowledge/generative.py):
  the LLM integration point, opt-in only, grounded strictly in the
  passages the retriever already ranked - not wired into any default
- New CLI command: mars-ai-os knowledge-demo
- 44 new tests (full suite: 44 passed), ruff check clean

Follow-up (not in this PR): a real SourceConnector for public Mars
datasets (NASA PDS / ADS / arXiv) - selecting and vetting APIs is
next per docs/ROADMAP.md Phase 1.
